HEADWORD: Rictus
<hw>Ric"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., the aperture
of the mouth.]</ety> <def>The gape of the mouth, as of birds; -- often
resricted to the corners of the mouth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

